2026-05-09  M02 Arc 4 redrafted again after owner feedback reshaped the ultrawide vision. Two big changes: (a) at the ultrawide breakpoint, the left rail IS the Initiatives index — same data, same components in compressed form — not a bespoke widget alongside it. The whole account is in chrome; the main column is the current Initiative; the right rail stays as today's Details slot. (b) People in the cross-Initiative pane can be dragged directly onto an Initiative entry in the rail to add them as a member; click on a person remains the keyboard / a11y / non-drag path, now correctly supporting BOTH add and remove (prior single-action draft was a misread by the agent). Item count grew 8 → 12: container max-width refresh; right-rail sizing at xl/2xl; task-row breathing room at xl/2xl; index grid expansion at xl/2xl; ultrawide breakpoint above 2xl; left-rail = Initiatives index in chrome; main empty state at /initiatives on ultrawide ("pick one"); click the current Initiative on the rail to close it (navigate back to /initiatives); cross-Initiative people pane; click-to-add-or-remove (item 10); drag-to-add (item 11, drag-to-remove intentionally NOT a gesture); mobile flyout for the left rail mirroring the right-rail flyout from Arc 2 item 16 — affordance only appears on /initiatives/:id, not on the index. Cross-cutting requirements gained a "drag a11y" rule (every drag-to-add must be achievable via click-to-add). Open Questions cleaned up: dropped "/initiatives ultrawide redirect" (answered: no redirect, just empty-state main), kept default-role-on-add (now applies to both items 10 and 11), added drop-target visual feedback question. Implementation Notes gained an "index-as-rail reuse" note insisting on a single shared component with a `compact` variant rather than two parallel widgets. Arc 3 doc updated with a Cross-arc note: drag infrastructure must be reusable for Arc 4 item 11; favors a small custom hook over a heavy library that only fits one of the two cases. Milestone rollup table item count updated 8 → 12; PLAN.md updated. Still pending owner approval before implementation.
2026-05-15  M02 renamed from "UX Overhaul" to "UX Buildout". "Overhaul" implied an existing UX being reworked; M01 was less of a complete app than that framing suggested, and M02 is really constructing the UX, not refurbishing one. Scope of the rename: `docs/milestones/m02-ux-overhaul/` directory → `docs/milestones/m02-ux-buildout/`; milestone file `m02-ux-overhaul.md` → `m02-ux-buildout.md`; doc title `# M02-UX-Overhaul` → `# M02-UX-Buildout`; PLAN.md references; m03-api.md precondition reference; parent-link sweep across all five arc files (`m02.01` … `m02.05`); git branch `M02-ux-overhaul` → `M02-ux-buildout` (local + origin). Arc files retain their numeric-slug names (`m02.NN-*`) — unaffected by the milestone-slug change. Past CHANGELOG entries and prior commit messages keep the old name as historical record.
2026-05-19  M02 Arc 3 horizontal drag mode rolled back. In-browser testing of items 4–5 surfaced that horizontal cursor-position-as-depth is non-obvious and the snap-back band only manages ambiguity that the mode itself introduces; keyboard Alt+←/→ (item 6) already covers indent / dedent cleanly. Items 4, 5, and 10 marked superseded in place; new item 13 describes the single-mode vertical drag (drop on a row → child of that row, no horizontal sensitivity, no indent guide, no snap-back band). Testing sub-subitems 11.4.2 / 11.4.3 / 11.4.4 / 11.8.5 retired. Sibling reorder via drag intentionally NOT addressed by this rollback — owner has flagged it as forthcoming Arc 3 work paired with a broader sibling sort-order toolset (design pending); keyboard Alt+↑/↓ remains the sibling-reorder path until then. Code strip in assets/js/app.js follows in its own commit.
